Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[1]: "Today we'll be talking about the older gods."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[2]: "Religion in general seems to go on deaf ears these days
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[3]: "I understand the ancient rites and Sunday churches must
seem ridiculous, but at the same time there is a lot of
cultural history buried in what we call religion."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[4]: "Many everyday tasks are given a proper time thanks to
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[5]: "Be it meditating under the guise of praying or sending off
our friends and family to the beyond with funeral rituals."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[6]: "Of course I'm not saying you should believe that bullshit
Kings and sultans practically wrote all those holy books."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[7]: "Those texts are mostly just for crowd control and getting
peasants to behave in fear of greater powers."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[8]: "But let's get to the topic - Gro-goroth and Sylvian."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[9]: "Destruction and Creation. They say one could not exist
without the other... What do you weasels think?"
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[12: "Yeah, they co-exist in perfect balance. That's why they
are the most famous older gods to exist."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[14: "I say there are no stupid answers..."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[15: "...Only stupid people. You are wrong, you imbecile."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[18: "Well whatdya know. Sometimes you manage to spew some
words of wisdom too by accident."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[19: "Well whatdya know, kueh kueh. Sometimes you manage to spew
some words of wisdom too by accident."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[21: "Shut it while you're still ahead of the game!"
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[22: "In the grand scheme of things, where does the Moon god
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[23: "Were you dropped on your head as a baby? NO! I bet you
were thrown into a wall! That's what you'd deserve at least."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[24: "I said we talk about the Gro-goroth and Sylvian! WHY THE
HELL WOULD YOU BRING UP THE MOON GOD?!"
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[25: "No answers? Well that's for the better. No one wants to
hear you miserable worms utter words."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[26: "The idea that destruction and creation depend on each
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[27: "You can always destroy without giving anything back!"
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[28: "I'VE DESTROYED ENTIRE ARMIES DURING THE GREAT WARS OF THE
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[29: "And I've never created anything in return. I take what is
mine and that is the rule of nature."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[30: "So no matter what anyone else might say, if you study the
ways of the Gro-goroth, you will increase your chances for
survival in this wicked world by a shit-ton."
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[31: "That is probably the best advice I can give you as your
Map180.Event[32].Page[1].list.message[32: "So that about settles it. I'm off."
